modules.description: Handles HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 protocol stacks with TLS integration, using TCP/IP abstractions for network communication. Processes incoming requests and manages connection lifecycles within a unified event loop. Supports server-side TLS termination and protocol negotiation for secure, high-performance web services.

Provides functions to construct and send HTTP requests with specific methods, including handling headers, bodies, and chunked encoding. Works with URI structures, connection contexts, and network endpoints, supporting both HTTP and HTTPS protocols. Enables direct HTTP method calls like GET, POST, and PATCH, as well as form submissions and custom request handling.
